cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the application of game theory in the context of network/cybersecurity, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), or cs.CY (Computers and Society) due to its focus on modelling the interactions of decision makers in security problems who compete for limited and shared resources.
